id: pm-w89s
title: "As an integrator, I can build a complete custom PM tool for my project using only the public pm SDK"
description: "Agent-story capability statement for the SDK-first epic pm-usfg. Delivered when every CLI capability is reachable programmatically: an SDK-only consumer performs the full item lifecycle, queries, annotations, governance checks, and schema/profile customization without invoking the pm binary. Duplicate check: existing agent stories cover extension authoring, not SDK-only PM-tool assembly."
type: Story
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-story,"area:sdk",changelog-exclude
created_at: "2026-07-05T04:52:38.434Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-17T04:40:36.514Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-16T21:18:44.175Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 30
acceptance_criteria: "Exemplar package builds a minimal custom PM CLI importing only @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk; it exercises create/update/close/claim, list/search/context, comments/notes/files/deps, validate/health, and a schema customization end-to-end in its linked tests; no src/core deep imports anywhere in the exemplar"
parent: pm-usfg
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: "Fulfilled via PR#575's SDK-only exemplar (docs/examples/sdk-custom-tool): an integrator can build a complete custom PM tool — custom types/statuses, lifecycle, graph, context, search, validation, health — from only the public pm SDK."
expected_result: Integrator story satisfiable end-to-end with only public @unbrained/pm-cli/sdk exports.
actual_result: Exemplar shipped and verified from installed tarball in PR#575 (merged 2026-07-16); all six SDK promotion slices public; no private-core imports required.
